# Eligibility routine

Use the runtime-backed eligibility result as the truth layer when reasoning about candidates, forms, or collection tables.

## Rules

- Keep governance and user-facing usability in parallel rather than letting one silently erase the other.
- Keep analog weighting reproducible; seed and argv shape must explain the hierarchy.
- Treat observations as annotations on top of the hierarchy, not as substitutes for it.
- Credit each collection row to its source pass and source artifact.
- Keep server responsibility exclusive; do not let form compilation turn the package into a general alignment layer.

## Output discipline

- Show the seed and argv signature when summarizing a run.
- Keep row and column output formula-ready.
- Keep rule, agent, and skill projections clearly marked as projections.
